title: Anecdotes in American English (gnv64)
description:
Leslie A. Hill is an internationally known ELT expert who has published, in a number of different countries, about 240 books in the field of ELT plus gramophone records, tapes and lessons for Educational Television Overseas. He is the Chairman of Hill Publications Limited and based in the Channel Islands, UK.

These titles are a series of humorously illustrated readers published by Oxford University Press in the early 80's. All are scanned PDFs:

1. Elementary Anecdotes in American English (14.1 mb)
  
2. Intermediate Anecdotes in American English (15.5 mb)
  
3. Advanced Anecdotes in American English (16.3 mb)
